OL,6,FLewis-Ranwell later sued G4S Health
OL,7,FServices (UK), Devon & Cornwall
OL,8,FPolice, Devon Partnership NHS Trust,
OL,9,Fand Devon County Council, claiming all
OL,10,Ffour were negligent in their treatment
OL,11,Fof him.
OL,13,FThe Court of Appeal was told that he
OL,14,Falleges "it should have been obvious
OL,15,Fto all concerned during both
OL,16,Fdetentions that if he were released
OL,17,Fthere was a real risk that he would
OL,18,Finjure other people and that the
OL,19,Fnecessary steps should have been taken
OL,20,Fto keep him in detention until it was
OL,21,Fsafe for him to be released".
