OL,3,CMan who killed three pensioners can
OL,4,Ccontinue negligence claims, judges rule
OL,6,FUnder an "illegality defence", they
OL,7,Fargued that he should not be allowed
OL,8,Fto bring a claim based on the
OL,9,Fconsequences of his "three unlawful
OL,10,Fhomicides".
OL,12,FLewis-Ranwell's legal team argued the
OL,13,Fnot guilty verdict by reason of
OL,14,Finsanity was an acquittal, so under
OL,15,Fthe law he was not treated as
OL,16,Fcriminally responsible for his actions
OL,17,Fand could bring his claim.
